Arduino RFID door lock
===========================
This is an RFID authentication arduino project to provide power to a solenoid door lock.

* Door locking (default implementation)

[[to-do]] Here it is in action:
###add video


Hardware
--------
To make this RFID system, you'll need the following hardware:

* 1 x Arduino Ethernet - ([Coolcomponents](http://www.coolcomponents.co.uk/catalog/arduino-ethernet-with-module-p-760.html) [arduino.cc](http://arduino.cc/en/Main/Buy))
* 1 x Solenoid door lock ([Solenoid](http://www.tlc-direct.co.uk/Main_Index/Security_Menu_Index/CCTV_New_Index/Door_Entry_Index/Dook_Electric_Locks/index.html)
* 1 x RFID Reader module - Stronglink SL018 ([Stronglink](http://www.stronglink-rfid.com/en/rfid-modules/sl018.html)
* Some jumper wires to wire the whole thing together
* Some bell wire (anywhere on ebay)


